  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Due to antigenic changes of influenza viruses, the virus strains used in influenza vaccines
      are adjusted every year according to WHO and CPMP recommendations. Immunogenicity and
      tolerability of the newly composed vaccines are subject for evaluation in a yearly clinical
      trial in non-elderly adults and elderly subjects (CPMP/BWP/214/96).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
